# UI Design System Rules

## Core Principles (Stripe-Level)

### Immutable Boundaries
- **Never change business logic** — do not modify backend/firebase logic, auth flows, or data processing
- **Never change Firebase collections** — no schema changes, no new collections, no field renames
- **Never change authentication** — preserve all sign-in/sign-up flows, auth guards, and session logic
- **Only improve UI** — all changes must be purely presentational (styles, layout, animations, accessibility, micro-interactions)
- **Maintain existing functionality** — every button, link, form, and interaction must work exactly as before, just look/feel better

### Tech Stack (Must Use)
| Technology | Purpose |
|------------|---------|
| **Framer Motion** | Animations, page transitions, micro-interactions, layout animations |
| **shadcn/ui** | Dialog, Sheet, Toast, Tooltip, Dropdown, Popover, etc. (dark theme) |
| **Tailwind CSS** | All styling — utility-first, no custom CSS unless absolutely needed |
| **Mobile First** | Every component starts at 375px viewport, then scales up |
| **Accessibility (a11y)** | WCAG 2.1 AA minimum — focus rings, aria, keyboard nav, contrast |

## Design Philosophy
This project uses a **dark-luxury** aesthetic with gold accents. Every UI decision should reinforce: **premium, trustworthy, sophisticated, and warm** — think Stripe's polish with a warmer, gold-toned palette.

## Brand Colors

| Token | Hex | Usage |
|-------|-----|-------|
| `--gold-primary` | `#D4AF37` | Primary actions, active states, key highlights |
| `--gold-soft` | `#E6C97A` | Hover states, secondary gold elements |
| `--bg-main` | `#000000` | Page background |
| `--bg-section` | `#000000` | Section backgrounds |
| `--bg-card` | `#0A0A0A` | Card backgrounds |
| `--text-heading` | `#FFFFFF` | All headings (h1-h5) |
| `--text-body` | `#E5E5E5` | Body text, paragraphs |
| `--text-muted` | `#9A9A9A` | Secondary text, placeholders, timestamps |

## Typography

### Font Families
- **Headings (h1-h5)**: `"Playfair Display", Georgia, serif` — weight 600, letter-spacing -0.02em
- **Body**: `"Inter", system-ui, sans-serif`

### Heading Hierarchy
- Headings use `var(--text-heading)` (white)
- Body text uses `var(--text-body)` (light gray)
- Muted/small text uses `var(--text-muted)` (mid gray)

### Tailwind Aliases
- `font-heading` → Playfair Display (serif)
- `font-body` → Inter / system-ui (sans-serif)

## Background Pattern
The body has a subtle radial gradient:
```css
background: #000000;
background-image: 
  radial-gradient(ellipse at 20% 50%, rgba(212, 175, 55, 0.02) 0%, transparent 50%),
  radial-gradient(ellipse at 80% 50%, rgba(212, 175, 55, 0.02) 0%, transparent 50%);
background-attachment: fixed;
```

## Component Classes

### Cards
| Class | When to Use |
|-------|-------------|
| `card-premium` | Elevated content cards (hover lifts, gold border on hover) |
| `card-glass-premium` | Cards over dynamic backgrounds (blur, hover lift) |
| `card-glass` | Simple glass overlay panels |
| `card-transparent` | Category/list cards (subtle hover) |

### Buttons
| Class | When to Use |
|-------|-------------|
| `btn-primary` | Primary CTA — gold gradient on black background |
| `btn-outline` | Secondary actions — white border, gold border on hover |
| `btn-ghost` | Tertiary/icon buttons — muted text, gold on hover |

### Glassmorphism
| Class | When to Use |
|-------|-------------|
| `glass` | Light glass overlay (blur-12, border-white/08) |
| `glass-strong` | Strong glass (blur-16, border-white/10) |

### Navigation (Mobile-specific)
- Use `sticky-bottom-cta` for fixed bottom action bars on mobile
- Add `pb-mobile-cta` as padding-bottom on pages with sticky CTAs
- Use `floating-cta` for a fixed circular CTA button (bottom 80px, right 20px)
- Always set `padding-bottom: 80px` on mobile pages that use sticky bottom elements

### Badges
| Class | When to Use |
|-------|-------------|
| `badge-verified` | Verified/badge indicators — green pill style |

### Filter Tabs
| Class | When to Use |
|-------|-------------|
| `filter-tab` | Filter/pill buttons — gold gradient when `.active` |

### Progress Bars
| Class | When to Use |
|-------|-------------|
| `progress-active` | In-progress state (blue gradient) |
| `progress-expiring` | Expiring soon (amber gradient) |
| `progress-complete` | Completed (green gradient) |

### Inputs
| Class | When to Use |
|-------|-------------|
| `input` | Text inputs — transparent bg, gold border on focus |

### Touch Feedback
- Add `touch-feedback` class on interactive elements for a subtle press effect (scale 0.97)

## Layout Guidelines

1. **Page Structure**: Standard pages use a centered layout with `max-w-7xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8`
2. **Sections**: Content sections use `py-8` to `py-16` depending on importance
3. **Responsive**: Mobile-first approach. Mobile breakpoint at 640px.
4. **Spacing**: Use consistent spacing — gap-4/gap-6 for grids, p-4/p-6 for cards
5. **Borders**: All borders use `rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.08)` neutral, or gold tinted for interactive states

## Firestore UI Patterns

### Active/Expired Match States
When displaying time-sensitive data from Firestore:
- **Active**: Show green progress bar (`progress-active`) or gold indicator
- **Expiring Soon** (< 2h): Show amber warning (`progress-expiring`)
- **Expired**: Show completed state (`progress-complete`) or strikethrough text

### Loading States
- Use skeleton shimmer animation for card/row loading
- Center spinner within the container
- For Firestore data, always show a loading state while fetching, then a fallback message if none found

## Animation Principles
- Default transition: `all 0.3s cubic-bezier(0.4, 0, 0.2, 1)`
- Touch feedback: `transform 0.15s cubic-bezier(0.4, 0, 0.2, 1)`
- Hover lift: `translateY(-2px)` on cards
- Avoid heavy animations on page load — prefer subtle micro-interactions
- Only apply scale transforms on hover-capable devices (`@media (hover: hover)`)

## Accessibility & UX
- All interactive elements need `cursor: pointer`
- Use `aria-current="page"` for active navigation items
- Provide `alt` text on all images
- Maintain minimum contrast ratios: white (#FFFFFF) on dark backgrounds passes AAA
- Gold (#D4AF37) should not be used as the only color indicator — pair with text/icons
- `btn-primary` (gold on black) provides sufficient contrast for CTAs

